RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14500. (PLUS UP TO $2,900 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALTAMONTES DIVA vied for the lead from the inside down the backstretch, was under a steady hand drive on the turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch to kick clear under a strong drive and prevail in the end. MISS DISTINCTIVE was off slowly at the start, was moving up along the inside swiftly, came out three wide in the upper stretch and closed willingly. GREATEST GLORY lead the way early, then vied with in inner foe into the turn, was in a hard drive then gave way in late stretch. HAL'S DREAM chased the pace while three wide, bid on the turn, then flattened out in the stretch. SEXY RAGS raced in the four path down the backstretch, then dueled to avoid last place with an inner rival throughout the turn and into the stretch and was up at the wire. INDY LOVER chased the pace from the two path, then dueled to avoid last place throughout the second half and was last in the end.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 57. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $1,650 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. (If Deemed inadvi sable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLOOD ORANGE unhurried early to be at the rear of the field, crept closer down the backside, unleashed a strong five wide rally in the turn to sweep to the lead, cleared in upper stretch and drew off down the lane as much best. RIVER'S END was carried well wide in the first turn by rival, dropped inside that one to stalk the pace down the backside, overtook the pacesetter turning for home but was immediately passed by the winner and kept on gamely to be second best. GOLD MEMORIES rated in mid-pack comfortably within striking distance, well positioned to make his rally at the quarter pole and lacked a late response when called upon for the drive. LA VALEDORA reserved off the pace to settle in mid-field, saved ground while rallying along the rail and made up ground late. THEHUNKSCLASSYLADY moved up in the first turn to take the lead down the backside, set a pressured pace to the head of the lane and weakened down the stretch. RON'S LAVENDER went evenly never posing a threat. MEMORABLE FLIGHT sped to the lead down the lane the first time, bore out significantly in the first turn carrying out RIVER'S END, raced wide down the backside and failed to navigate the far turn as well, racing wide again and dropped back from contention.

ADELE'S BLING was fanned six wide in the first turn, dropped near the back of the field and went evenly. KAYLEE'S SHADOW stalked the pace for a half mile and came up empty. HIGH DEF RIDGE fanned very wide in the first turn, dropped to the rear of the field and was never a factor.

EMMYLOU SQUALL raced in the middle of the field while five wide, then steadily lost ground throughout the second half and was no menace. UNION BABE chased the pace from the two path down the early backstretch, then dropped back and failed to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 79. Claiming Purse 18500. (PLUS UP TO $3,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over th e Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRAIGHT LUCK sped to the early lead after breaking alertly, was carried wide into the turn to avoid the rider-less horse, dropped back in while re-gaining stride, pursued the leader through the lane and gamely wore that one down to take command in deep stretch as clearly the best. DRAG MALIBU prompted the early pace from three wide, assumed command when the winner was carried wide, responded when challenged in upper stretch but could not hold off the winner in a good try. TEAM LEADER rated in mid-pack early to track the leaders, rallied three wide turning for home and made a steady gain to be up for the show. WITT AMERICA bumped at the start by inside rival, raced up into contention to stalk the pace, checked into the turn when encountering traffic due to the loose horse, re-gained stride and finished evenly to hit the board in a rough trip. HARD CANDY checked off heels in traffic just before the turn, tracked the leaders to upper stretch, made a mild rally down the lane while being squeezed again in mid-stretch. JUST OKIE went evenly and was never a factor. SONGWRITER prominent in the early going but lacked a rally fading in the lane. MOONSHINE STEVE steadied briefly away from the gate, dropped to the rear of the field and was no threat. PITALE leaned out at the start, lost rider a few strides from the gate, rushed up the inside rail to be in front and bolted to the outside fence into the turn to interfere with the winner and cause traffic problems for much of the field.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAYLOR'S SECRET rushed up the fence to duel on the lead down the backside, was headed at the quarter pole and sawed off in upper stretch when the pacesetter dropped in, took up sharply, was gathered up and re-set to a drive and was just up in time from between horses in a very game effort. SWEET BAY stalked the pace from three wide through the turn, was put to an early drive to loom in upper stretch and kept on down the lane. PAISLEY CROSS took command leaving the gate, dueled with the winner through the turn, shook free turning for home, dropped over impeding the winner in upper stretch, dug-in down the lane but tired late in the drive. BEBOP BABY went evenly and never menaced. ICY CAPE was never a threat from an inside trip. MY BABYS GONE prominently placed early and came up empty dropping back through the field.
